Trends in the development of society and their impact on customer behaviour. Opportunities and threats of user segmentation. Models of customer behaviour analysis. Influencers of customer behaviour. Peculiarities of the analysis of private and business clients.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to develop the ability to understand and influence customer behaviour in the context of organizational behaviour and psychology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the history of the development of the customer behaviour theory and related terms; 2) is able to analyse user experience and behaviour in different service situations; 3) can segment customers and analyse their needs/expectations; 4) knows the theories describing the process of customer behaviour and the influencing factors of customer behaviour.
